rComments: One of the worst profs I've ever had in uoft. Extremely condescending. She looks like you owe her $500000 when you ask her any questions. Her test questions are extremely ambiguous and marked harshly.
Lectures are very clear and insightful. Tests reflect what she taught. Content is complex but easy to understand if you listen. The tests will determine if you really understood the material.
I have never had a professor as rude and condescending as her. She fails to answer emails, and writes ambiguous multiplce choice questions, sometimes with no correct answer.

The lecture content is quite interesting and the guest lecturers teach very well. However, the tests are extremely specific and you need to study everything. Mitchell is really condescending and doesnt know how to simplify concepts, makes it very difficult to ask her questions. The assignment was marked very harshly.
